      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Preheat your oven to 180°C/350°F/Gas mark 4.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cream the butter and both sugars together until the mixture is pale and light.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Gradually add the beaten eggs, mixing well between each addition.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Dissolve the coffee in the boiling water, add to the mixture and mix to combine.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Sift the flour and a pinch of salt into the bowl, add the chopped walnuts and fold in using a large metal spoon or rubber spatula until the mixture is smooth.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Divide the mixture between the Mini Sandwich Tin (roughly 1 heaped dessertspoon of mixture in each well) and level with a teaspoon.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bake on the middle shelf of the hot oven for about 15 minutes. The cakes should be golden and well risen. Test with a wooden skewer in the middle of one cake. It should come out clean.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Leave the cakes to rest in the tin for 2 minutes then ease out onto a wire cooling rack and leave until cold.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "To make the buttercream, cream the butter and icing sugar together until the mixture is pale and light. Dissolve the coffee in the boiling water, add to the mixture and mix until thoroughly combined.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Cut the cakes in half and spread the bottom layers with half of the buttercream. Spread the top of the cakes with the remaining buttercream and gently press the two halves together. Top each cake with a walnut half to serve.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Test with a skewer. It should come out with a few moist crumbs, not wet batter. Don't open the oven before three-quarters of the bake time.",
              "cause": "Underbaked, or the oven door opened too early.",
              "symptom": "Cake sinks in the middle"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Check at the minimum bake time and every five minutes after. Weigh flour for cake recipes, cup measures vary by 20% depending on how you scoop.",
              "cause": "Overbaked, or too much flour measured by cup not weight.",
              "symptom": "Cake is dry"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Drop the temperature by 10°C and check earlier. Domed cakes can be trimmed flat once cool.",
              "cause": "Oven too hot, or batter too thick.",
              "symptom": "Top cracked or domed"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Check baking powder is fresh. It loses lift after six months. Use room-temperature butter and eggs so the batter holds air.",
              "cause": "Raising agent stale or omitted, or butter and eggs cold.",
              "symptom": "Cake didn't rise"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Variations",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Citrus version: replace the vanilla with the zest of an orange or lemon.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Nut-free: swap ground almonds for desiccated coconut or extra plain flour, weight for weight.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A British home cook's dish. It sits among the recipes families remember without thinking about, the kind that gets adjusted across generations and never quite the same twice.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
